## What I Am Still Thinking About

One thing I am genuinely uncertain about is the experience requirement for CGRC certification. ISC2 requires candidates to have relevant work experience in the field before the full certification is granted. For someone like me who is building their GRC knowledge through this kind of self-directed project rather than in a formal professional role, I am not sure exactly how that experience requirement applies.

I want to research this more carefully — whether project-based learning like this challenge counts toward the experience requirement, what the associate pathway looks like for candidates who do not yet meet the full requirement, and what the most realistic timeline is for pursuing the certification given where I am starting from. That research feels like an important next step alongside the technical learning.

